wmhdplop: wmhdplop ()
wmhdplop:
wmhdplop: wmhdplop is yet another dockapp for WindowMaker, or any
wmhdplop: windowmanager/desktop environment that handles dockapps (KDE has a
wmhdplop: dockbar extension, and gnome swallows). It monitors your hard-drives
wmhdplop: by sending visual stimuli to your cortex each time your /dev/hdx
wmhdplop: (or /dev/sdx) writes or reads anything. Try to launch openoffice and
wmhdplop: enjoy the wmhdplop show! (loading these kitties in mozilla also
wmhdplop: works). gkhdplop is the gkrellm port of wmhdplop.
wmhdplop: http://hules.free.fr/wmhdplop/
wmhdplop: Packager: _PACKAGER on _BUILD_DATE
